  "texts": [
    "It compares the original and restored images by considering the mean squared error between their pixel values.",
    "where, MAX is the maximum possible pixel value (255 for 8-bit images), MSE is the mean squared error between the original and denoised images.",
    "SSIM is applicable to image restoration as well.",
    "It assesses the similarity between the original and restored images in terms of luminance, contrast, and structure.",
    "Higher SSIM values indicate better restoration quality."
  ],
